I've been doing 3D for about 5 years, first starting out on Maya then finding my way onto Blender. The leaning curve is not as steep or long, but does require you to learn the technical side of things before getting started. Blender while not as powerful as Maya/ Z-brush is such a nice tool for Freelancers and Hobbyists due the amount it gives you (not to mention all of the plug-ins you can tact onto it).
